Package de.hshannover.dqgui.framework.model

Class ObjectWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.hshannover.dqgui.framework.model.ObjectWrapper
  • public class ObjectWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    Allows to wrap a generic object in a nullsafe way and hide the fact that it is generic to allow the framework to find a matching constructor when using i.e. a method to inject a list of dependencies.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      <T> T unpack()
      Unpacks the object via type inference.
      If you pack wrap a List<String> in here you could unpack it like this: List<String> = obj.unpack();
      This spares you from casting the object yourself but does not protect you from a class cast exception.
